stimulus: Welcome to the experiment! Press any key to begin.

You will see a series of abstract figures. They are adaptations of signs in the Korean alphabet, but that is not important for this study.

Abstract figures sometimes have a more masculine or feminine shape. Here, each figure has already been assigned a gender as Male or Female by a panel of respondents in a pilot study. The respondents were not given specific instructions on how to do this, but were only told to use their intuition and to take into account the entire configuration of the stimulus.

Your task now is to guess the assigned gender of each figure. Please press the corresponding response keys to indicate your choice:

Male → , (comma)

Female → . (period)

Press either response keys to continue.

Your choice is correct if it matches the gender assigned by the majority of respondents in the pilot study.

For each correct choice you will receive 2 cents. There will be 200 trials divided into 4 blocks of 50 trials. You will be able to take a break after every 50 trials.

Press the space bar to continue.

Here are some examples.

For each, guess whether the assigned figure is male-like or female-like and indicate your choice by pressing either response keys.

Press the space bar to continue.
Let us begin! Press the space bar when you are ready to start block 1 of 4.

Good job, block 1 complete! Please take a moment to rest.

When you are ready to continue with block 2 of 4, press the space bar.

Half way there! Please take a moment to rest.

When you are ready to continue with block 3 of 4, press the space bar.

One more block to go! Please take a moment to rest.

When you are ready to continue with block 4 of 4, press the space bar.

Phase I of the experiment is complete.

Press the space bar to proceed to Phase II of the experiment.

Now we are interested in how well you can predict patterns in the series of figures. You will be asked to predict whether the next figure in the series is more male-like or female-like. When you see the Next Figure prompt, press the corresponding response keys to indicate your prediction:

Male → , (comma)

Female → . (period)

The actual figure will then appear on the screen. After you see the figure, please guess the assigned gender with response keys.

As before, you will receive 2 cents for correctly classifying each figure.

Press either response keys to continue.

PREDICTION BONUS

Your prediction accuracy is the total number of correct predictions you make over the 200 trials.

In addition to the 2 cents per correct figure classification, you have the chance to receive a bonus of 40 dollars IF your accuracy is above average relative to previous participants.

If your accuracy is below average relative to previous participants, then you will not receive the 40 dollar bonus.

Press the space bar to continue.

Here are some examples.

For each, predict whether the next figure looks more male-like or female-like. Then, when the figure appears, guess whether it looks more male-like or female-like and indicate your choice.

Press the space bar to continue.
